TITLE: Accessing Form Errors with getError in Vue
DESCRIPTION: Example of using the getError function from useForm to access specific field errors. This approach allows you to get the error of a particular field, returning undefined if no error exists.
SOURCE: https://github.com/formwerkjs/formwerk.dev/blob/main/src/content/docs/guides/forms/index.mdx#2025-04-13_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: vue
CODE:
```
<script setup lang="ts">
import { useForm } from '@formwerk/core';
import TextField from './TextField.vue';
import { z } from 'zod';

const { handleSubmit, getError } = useForm({
  schema: z.object({
    url: z.string().url().max(8),
    email: z.string().email(),
  }),
});
</script>

<template>
  <TextField name="url" label="URL" required />
  <TextField name="email" label="Email" required />

  <ul>
    <li>URL Error: {{ getError('url') }}</li>
    <li>Email Error: {{ getError('email') }}</li>
  </ul>
</template>
```

